My husband and I went in for dinner around 530 on a Thursday night. It was our first time here. They were busy, but still had several tables open. We were immediately served with water by some man, and had some menus thrown at us by some woman. This was our greeting. Over 15 minutes passed, and we saw who I assumed was our waitress numerous times. She would not make eye contact with us, even as she waited on the table directly next to us. I was confused and thought maybe we were to order at the bar, and when i tried that the bartender said, no, i will send your waitress right over. A woman named Haley (I only know her name as it appeared on the receipt) appeared at our table to take our order. She was fake friendly and seemed annoyed, and said 'we are really busy'. My husband was still a little nauseous from our visit at the university hospital, and wanted to take his food to go, while I wanted to eat there. Around 20 minutes later she brought our food out, both in to go boxes. She said sorry the cook didnt listen to me when i told him only 1 was to go. So I ate my dinner out of the box at the table, awkward. The chicken sandwich was good, the fries were so so. She asked if we wanted the check right away, and I said yes. We immediately put our debit card in the slot and she walked past it in a hurry several times. We tried to get her attention to no avail. We had to get up and hunt her down to pay after waiting 20 more minutes. She was very attentive to the table directly next to us, while we were completely ignored. Needless to say, we will never be back.

I was leaving a show a couple of weeks ago and the cops roll up on me before I even put the car in gear, saying they saw me "stumbling".  Well, that's what apparently what they call it when you walk carefully on an inch-thick, sheet of glazed ice in zero degree weather at 11:00 pm.  I got to do a field sobriety test - they were visibly upset when I passed their breathalyzer and they couldn't arrest me.  I know, cool story.  I'll be using the parking garage next time.
